# 🔒 NEVER commit secrets

Full policy: see `AGENTS.md`.

Never stage/commit/push real API keys, OAuth client secrets (`GOCSPX-…`), Google API keys
(`AIza…`), AWS keys (`AKIA…`), or passwords.

Real values live only in gitignored `.env` / `.env.production`. Only `*.example` templates
with placeholders are committed. OAuth client IDs in `VITE_*` are public (baked into the
bundle) and OK; client secrets/keys must never be in this frontend repo.

Before committing: review `git diff --staged` for secrets; never `git add -A` blindly;
never remove `.gitignore` entries that protect `.env` files.
